==English==
===Etymology===
[[lobster]] + [[back]], from the resemblance to lobsters of the red coats worn by the British soldiers

===Noun===
'''lobsterback''' (''plural'' '''lobsterbacks''')

#(''derogatory'') A name given by patriots and rebels to British soldiers during the [[w:American Revolution|American Revolution]].

